Ocean Map Portal 0.3.0
======================

"Behold me fettered, clamped to these rough rocks, even as a ship is moored
 fast by timid sailors, fearful of night because of the roaring sea."
 --Prometheus Lyomenos, Aeschylus

New Features:

 - Reorient to be variable driven, totally new control panel (Danni)
 - Unit and acceptance tests (Danni)
 - Select any past map layer from Outputs (Danni)
 - No more ExtJS [faster loading] (Danni)
 - Parallelise plotting (Danni)
 - New periods: Reynolds/ERSST/BRAN 3/6/12 month (mean) (Nick)
 - New variables: anom/dec for Reynolds/ERSST multi-month
 - New generic processing script (Nick)

Bugs Fixed:

 - Refactor SST classes (Danni)
 - Fix rounding bug in lat/lon displays (Danni)
 - Improve scalebar readability (Nick)
 - Improve plots, move all plots to the generic plotter (Nick)
 - Drive regions listing from backend (Danni)
 - WCAG fixes (Danni)
 - Separate out control panel from other frontend components (Danni)
 - Subset Reynolds/ERSST datasets (Nick)
 - Ensure contour labels are shown for Reynolds/ERSST (Nick)
 - Autoguess plot resolution (with optional per-region override) (Danni)
 - IE8 fixes (Danni)
 - Plot fixes (Nick)
 - Fix typo to ERSST About file (Danni)
 - Compatibility fixes for standard RHEL6 libraries (Danni)
 - Gracefully fail for requests outside data range (Danni)
 - Add contour lines to decile plots (Nick)
 - Update Reynolds start date (Nick)
 - Fix bug where map wouldn't change position with some screen sizes (Danni)
 - Fix bug where double-clicking caused map to jump (Danni)
 - Report error when sealevel data is out of bounds or on land (Danni)

Ocean Map Portal 0.2.0
======================

"小娃撑小艇" (A little child paddles a little boat)
    --On the Lake, Bai Juyi

New Features:

 - Australian portal (Danni)
 - map tile caching and compression (Danni)
 - Improved layout on small screens, take advantage of available space (Danni)
 - Consistent look and feel (Danni)
 - 24 comparison plots (Danni)
 - New library versions: OpenLayers, ExtJS, jQuery (Danni)
 - Lat/lon markers automatically update from lat/lon changes (Danni)
 - Hover over tidal gauges to see their names (Danni)
 - Improved client side caching (Danni)
 - Compressing JS/CSS resources to reduce bandwidth (Danni)
 - Map improvements: landmask resolution, labels (Danni, Jason)
 - only showing COSPPac EEZs (Danni)
 - code cleanups (Danni and Nick)

Bugs Fixed:

 - remove white line on map at 180th meridian (Nick)
 - plotting fixes (Nick)
 - Fix date handling bugs in 31 day months (Danni)
 - handling the months August and September correctly (Danni)
 - general bug fixes (Danni, Nick, Jason)
 - Fix direction of wave roses (Jason)

Ocean Map Portal 0.1.0
======================

First release!

Features:

 - Package portal, remove hardcoded paths (Danni)
 - Filter date ranges based on dataset (Sheng)
 - Initial portal (Sheng)
 - BRAN 2.1 (Nick, Billie)
 - WW3 (Jason)
 - ERSST (Luke Guarde)
 - Reynolds SST (Matt Howie)
 - Sealevel (Luke Guarde, Danni)
 - About Files (Grant, Billie and Nick)

Bugs Fixed:

 - Standardise plots (Jason, Nick, Billie)
 - Give error when selected point on land (Jason)
 - Website doesn't render properly in IE (Danni)
 - General bug fixes (Danni, Sheng, Billie, Jason, Nick)
